Warsaw Stock Exchange, Kernel: Central Europe Equity Preview

-- B y   P i o t r   S k o l i m o w s k i
-- 
2011-10-03T04:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-02/warsaw-stock-exchange-kernel-central-europe-equity-preview.html
The following is a list of companies
whose shares may have unusual price changes in central European
markets. Stock symbols are in parentheses after company names.
Share prices are from the last close.  Poland ’s WIG20 Index closed unchanged, the Czech PX Index
lost 0.8 percent and  Hungary ’s BUX Index fell 0.2 percent.  The  Warsaw Stock Exchange (GPW)  : The operator of the
Polish equity market may pay as much as 230 million zloty ($69.7
million) for an 80 percent stake in state-owned power exchange
Towarowa Gielda Energii SA, known as PolPx, Rzeczpospolita
newspaper reported Oct. 1, without saying where it got the
information. The shares fell 0.5 percent to 42.5 zloty.  Kernel Holding SA (KER)  : The largest sunflower-oil
producer in Ukraine signed an agreement for a $100 million five-
year loan with a Ukrainian bank it didn’t name, the company said
in an regulatory filing on Oct. 1. Kernel will use the proceeds
to pay off the debt of its Ukrros unit and to finance sugar
production, according to the filing. Kernel rose 0.4 percent to
61.3 zloty.  To contact the reporters on this story:
Piotr Skolimowski in Warsaw at 
 pskolimowski@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gavin Serkin at 
